Response to Hernandez<br><br>
First. Read comments b/w me and others in (1)Comments about this site and (2) vet-not vets dialogue. Secondly, get a grip, so a little kid gave you a bad time in an airport, what about the 50,000 dead US Soldiers, or the over 1 million Viet's who didn't ask for the USA to INVADE their country. Third. No one, even you, HAD to serve. There was draft counselors and plenty of information out about how NOT to go.  Getting drafted (Oh.GEE, I didn't have any choice, I was drafted) just doesn't cut it any better than the Nazi's &quot;I was only following orders&quot; logic.  P.S. At the Nuremburg trials we (our parents) HUNG those who used that excuse. Fourth, 1000's of us as you say, attacked soldiers or anyone in a uniform. That's bullshit. Don't come in here with nonsense and bullshit, there are too many VETS and Protestors both who will back me on this. Lastly, sounds like you are blaming a life of &quot;bad housing, inadequate jobs, etc&quot; on being in Nam.  Thats BS too.  You are responsible for your life, no one else. That means whether or not you went to nam or to canada. Check out the rest of this site before you jump into something at mid point and without a paddle.  Try Tom Dier's Home page about nam, or the comments from srg4444@primenet.com (Stewart R. Gable) and then check you soul, as well as your six.  To say protestors divided a nation is absurd.  The reality check seems to be that you are a quart low and in denial (and I don't mean the river in egypt).  The war was wrong, the war divided America. Thanks for giving me so much power. If I had so much, I would have stopped it, wouldn't I.  After you think about all of this, and read the other comments, come back and get real.  I'll be here to educate you. ps. The name is spatz, not spata, which shows that you didn't read the back comments.   Please do.
